                       "message":  "VIEWMENU-RESETCAMERA-A4: add the View menu (Reset Camera) - substrate + wiring\n\nFourth and final beat of the menu-breadth arc (File #291, Edit #295, Play #297).\nUnlike the prior three (pure wiring), View needs a NEW runtime action: today the\ncamera is auto-framed only at construction; this adds a runtime \"frame the live\nscene\" reset and wires the View menu to it.\n\nSubstrate (editor-shell):\n- EditorShell::reset_camera() - reframe editor_camera to the isometric view of\n  the live scene\u0027s AABB union (compute_aabb_union + isometric_camera_for_bounds),\n  falling back to the default pose when nothing is frameable. Infallible.\n- current_scene_bounds() - sources the live renderable meshes the same way as\n  render_path Step 6 (prebuilt meshes, else the CAD projection mesh).\n\nWiring:\n- editor-egui-host: declare editor.main_menu.view, register \"Reset Camera\"\n  (Command::ResetCamera) on the shared MenuRegistry (build_main_menu_entries now\n  returns a 4-tuple), paint a 4th \"View\" menu_button.\n- editor-shell drain: route Command::ResetCamera -\u003e reset_camera() (no swallow -\n  infallible, unlike the Play items\u0027 route_play_button).\n\nTests: 3 editor-shell (frames prebuilt meshes; no-scene fallback to default;\nmenu route reframes via View) + 2 editor-egui-host (registry resolves Reset\nCamera; round-trips through the handoff).\n\nProduct semantics (owner-confirmed): \"frame the scene\", not a fixed default-pose\njump - matches the constructor\u0027s existing auto-frame. No new Command variant\n(ResetCamera already existed); no Cargo.toml change; forbidden-dep unchanged.\n\nThe View additions tipped editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs past 1000L (production\n~913L + inline tests ~120L), so a `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:` annotation is added at the\nfile head per the host.rs precedent (annotate in-the-moment; extract the inline\ntest module to a sibling file as a later dispatch). No exemptions.toml entry.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
