                       "message":  "VIEWMENU-RESETCAMERA-A4: widen remaining menu-set prose to include View\n\nCodex review of 865df1d caught 5 live source-doc/comment framings still saying\nFile + Edit + Play (or \"all three points\" / \"File, Edit, or Play\") after this PR\nadded the View menu - the same stale-prose class as #297. The EXEC pass widened\nthe spots in its edit regions but never ran the whole-crate multiline sweep.\n\nWidened (editor-egui-host, docs/comments only):\n- lib.rs:354 menu_command_handoff field doc (\"File + Edit + Play\" -\u003e \"+ View\")\n- lib.rs:390 play_menu_entries field doc (\"all three points\" -\u003e \"all four points\")\n- lib.rs:635 menu_command_handoff accessor doc (\"File + Edit + Play\" -\u003e \"+ View\")\n- lib.rs:801 render split-borrow comment (\"File + Edit + Play\" -\u003e \"+ View\")\n- handoff.rs:76-77 (WRAPPED across lines) struct doc (\"File, Edit, or Play\" -\u003e\n  \"File, Edit, Play, or View\")\n\nComplete multiline sweep now confirms zero stale framings remain: every\n\"File + Edit + Play\" carries \"+ View\"; no \"all three\" / \"Edit, or Play\" survive in\neither editor-egui-host or editor-shell. Docs-only; the .rs logic is byte-identical\nto the gate-passed 865df1d.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
